Association of Resident Doctors, Ondo State Teaching Hospital, Akure, yesterday embarked on indefinite strike over non-payment of their outstanding salaries and allowances. The doctors who vowed that they would never  resume until government look into their challenges and meet all their demands, expressed  disappointment over government’s inability to pay their salaries  despite their commitment to work. The leader of the doctors, Taiwo Olagbe, who stated this at a press conference in Akure, maintained that the medical practitioners have no  option than to embark on the indefinite strike. Olagbe said, “Having explored all peaceful avenues, expiration of the ultimatum, failed promises and non-challantant attitude of the management, we have no option than to take our destinies in our  hands.” The doctors disclosed that apart from non-payment of their outstanding salaries dated from September 2019 till May 2020, the government has also failed in providing Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) to its members at the forefront of the fight against COVID-19.   